\pard\f0\fs28 {\b 1. L. cernua} (L.) Pichi Serm., {\i Webbia}{\b  22:} 166 (1968) ({\i Lycopodium cernuum} L.,{\i  Lepidotis cernua} (L.) Beauv.). Main stem subterranean, creeping, woody, with erect, branched shoots up to 35 cm, the lower branches often rooting at tips. Fertile spikes 0·5-1 cm, ovoid, yellowish, at the end of short branches, ultimately nodding, with appressed, dentate sporophylls. {\i Açores.} *Az [Lu Si]. ({\i Tropics}.)
