\pard\f0\fs28 Leaves flat, linear to lanceolate, appressed or deflexed. Sporophylls different from the other leaves, broadly ovate to broadly lanceolate, with scarious, toothed margins. Sporangia opening at the apex; spores markedly muricate-reticulate. Prothallus holosaprophytic, disciform or tuberous, without appendages.
