\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. annotinum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 1103 (1753). Stems procumbent, widely creeping, branched; branches erect to ascending. Leaves 3-10 mm, linear-lanceolate to subulate, appressed to deflexed. Cones terminal on erect branches, sessile, solitary; sporophylls acute. 2n = 68.{\i  Heaths, mountain grassland and dwarf heath on mountains. N. Europe, extending southwards in the mountains to the Pyrenees, N. Appennini and S. Carpathians}. Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge He Ho Hs Hu It No Po Rm Rs(N, B, C, W, ?E) Su.
\par

