\pard\f0\fs28 Subsp.{\b  monostachyon} (Grev. & Hooker) Selander,{\i  Acta Phytogeogr. Suec.}{\b  28:} 7 (1950), a variant smaller in all its parts, leaves yellow-green, cones 1(2), 1-2·5 cm long, peduncles less than 3 cm, is common in the north of Fennoscandia, S. to 65° N.
