\pard\f0\fs28 Stems long, creeping, dorsiventral; branches forked several times and usually flabellate. Leaves 4-ranked, opposite and decussate, somewhat scale-like, the lateral leaves carinate. Cones terminal, the sporophylls different from the leaves; sporangia opening at the apex; spores markedly muricate-reticulate. Prothallus holosaprophytic. ({\i Diphasium} auct., non C. Presl)
